#: ../../A/annoyware.rst:5
msgid "annoyware"
msgstr "annoyware"

#: ../../A/annoyware.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../A/annoyware.rst:9
msgid ""
"A type of :ref:`shareware` that frequently disrupts normal program operation"
" to display requests for payment to the author in return for the ability to "
"disable the request messages. (Also called nagware) The requests generally "
"require user action to acknowledge the message before normal operation is "
"resumed and are often tied to the most frequently used features of the "
"software. See also :ref:`careware`\\, :ref:`charityware`\\, "
":ref:`crippleware`\\, :ref:`freeware`\\, :ref:`FRS`\\, :ref:`guiltware`\\, "
":ref:`postcardware`\\, and :ref:`suffix-ware`\\; compare :ref:`payware`\\."
msgstr ""
"正常なプログラム動作を頻繁に中断して、作者への支払いと引き換えにその要求メッセージを無効化できる権利を求める表示を出す類の\\ "
":ref:`shareware`\\ "
"。(nagwareとも呼ばれる。)この要求は通常、正常な動作が再開される前にメッセージを了承するユーザーの操作を必要とし、しばしばそのソフトウェアの最もよく使われる機能に結び付けられている。\\"
" :ref:`careware`\\ 、\\ :ref:`charityware`\\ 、\\ :ref:`crippleware`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`freeware`\\ 、\\ :ref:`FRS`\\ 、\\ :ref:`guiltware`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`postcardware`\\ 、\\ :ref:`suffix-ware`\\ も参照。\\ :ref:`payware`\\ "
"と比較せよ。"
